[3] Venezuela (Tachira)
Date: Sun 4 Apr 2010
Source: RCN [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.rcnradio.com/noticias/locales/04-04-10/incremento-de-casos-de-dengue-en-el-estado-t-chira>


The [number] of dengue cases in Tachira have increased. Authorities
of Environmental Health, the Mayor's office and Sanitary District III
agreed to work as a team to face the dengue threat that continues to
affect the population of Boliva municipality, where an average of 5
weekly cases are registered. Of these weekly reported cases, 4 are
[classical] dengue fever and one is DHF [This is a high ratio of DHF
cases compared to classical dengue cases. - Mod.TY]. In general,
children are the most affected by DHF.

There was a meeting and agreement to form a team to address this
problem and carry out an _Aedes_ survey in order to know about how
water catchments are handled in the affected areas. Also, an abate
[mosquito larvicide] application will be done to kill larvae, and
later they will carry out fumigation, said the epidemiologist.

An urgent meeting is expected in which Colombian and Venezuelan
health authorities will participate to halt this disease along the
border [of the 2 countries].

--
