[5] Paraguay (Asuncion)
Date: Sun 4 Apr 2010
Ultima Hora [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.ultimahora.com/notas/311140-Brote-de-dengue--2-en-Asunci%C3%B3n>


Dengue [virus] serotype 2 is circulating in Asuncion, which implies a
high risk of serious cases in the neighborhoods, according to the
Ministry of Public Health (MSP). The office of the Director General
of Health Surveillance identified a dengue [virus] 2 outbreak in the
Bernardino Caballero neighborhood of the capital. An active search
for febrile cases in the area, after finding the 1st affected
individual, led to the discovery of 9 dengue cases in this central
neighborhood. Dengue [viruses] type 1 and 3 have circulated
previously.

"This is a special alert call for Asuncion residents and for the
community of the capital, since dengue [virus] 2 could produce a
large-scale epidemic in Asuncion, if there are sufficient mosquitoes
to have transmission spread," said Dr. Ivan Allende, Director General
of Health Surveillance. He stressed that this possibility is real
when the infestation indices are around 5 percent, as in this case
[If this is a Breteau index, 5 percent is high according to WHO
standards and implies a significant risk of transmission. - Mod.TY].
Allende explained that during Holy Week [Easter week], efforts were
carried out to block virus transmission in the Bernardino Caballero
neighborhood.

To date, the Epidemiological Surveillance System has registered
notification of 5000 suspected dengue cases, of which 1828 have been
confirmed. "This gives us an incidence of 29 percent per 100 000
population, which signifies a low magnitude epidemic, considering the
numbers," noted Allende. None the less, he pointed out that
simultaneous circulation of the 3 [dengue virus] serotypes could
change this into a high-risk epidemic.

Since the beginning of the epidemic (in October 2009), 1828 dengue
cases have been confirmed. To date, 129 people have been
hospitalized. There are 5 deaths from dengue.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed-port@promedmail.org>

[In the Tue 6 Apr 2010 edition of Ultima Hora.com (in Spanish,
<http://www.ultimahora.com/notas/310698-Allende-afirma-que-la-epidemia-del-dengue-en-el-pa%C3%ADs-es-de-baja-magnitud>),
Allende warned that with the lower temperatures occurring currently,
the interior of homes provides an environment propitious for the
reproduction of the mosquito vector, so citizens must not lower their
guard.

