[6] Brazil (Ribeirao Preto, SP)
Date: Tue 6 Apr 2010
Source: Ribeirao Preto Online [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.ribeiraopretoonline.com.br/saude/epidemia-de-dengue-aumenta-e-chuva-pode-agravar-a-situacao-em-ribeirao-preto/34972>


This past Monday [5 Apr 2010], the Secretariat of Health of Ribeirao
Preto announced that the number of confirmed dengue cases in the city
reached 8495, an increase of 41.7 percent in relation to the total
[cases] registered in 2006, the year of the worst [dengue] epidemic
in the city. To get an idea, this increase exceeds the total number
of cases reported in 2009, 1694.

According to the Information System for Notifiable Diseases (SINAN)
of the state Secretariat of Health, Ribeirao Preto leads the state's
ranking for dengue in the 1st half of this year [2010]. In total,
there are 6928 victims of the [dengue virus transmtted by] the _Aedes
aegypti_ mosquito.

The Breteau index, which measures the infestation of _Aedes aegypti_,
also is high in the municipality. According to the World Health
Organization, the ideal is to have an index less than one percent,
whereas Ribeirao registers 2.8 percent.

The city government continues to request that the population help
with work to combat the disease, now that the Division of Vector
Control stated that 80 percent of the [mosquito] breeding sites are
within houses. Since the weather forecast for the next few days is
for rain and heat, a climate propitious for proliferation of the
mosquito, attention must be even greater. It is worth remembering
that this is the worst epidemic of the disease that Ribeirao Preto
has lived through.

A check of the number of cases in the city by region are: eastern
3419, south 2614, north 927, central 878 and east 657.

--
Communicated by:
HealthMap Alerts via ProMED-mail
<promed@promedail.org>

[The 4 Apr 2010 edition of A Cidade (in Portuguese,
<http://www.jornalacidade.com.br/editorias/cidades/2010/04/08/dengue-pode-ter-matado-mais-uma-pessoa-em-rp.html>)
reported that there have been 3 fatal cases of possible severe dengue
virus infections, 2 of which have been confirmed. This report
indicated that there were more than 10 000 dengue cases in the city,
43 of which have been of dengue with complications.

A map showing the states of Brazil can be accessed at
